Put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling add the @brown basmati rice{150%g} and cook at a rapid boil for ~{30%minutes}, or until soft.

Meanwhile, remove the root from the @spring onion{2.25}(thinly sliced, white and green parts separated) and thinly slice, keeping the white and green parts separate. Trim the tops from the @green beans{150%g} and chop into 3cm pieces. Halve, then remove the core from the @bell pepper{1}(halved and chopped into 2cm chunks). Halve the @red chilli{1/4}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Cut the tough base off the @lemongrass{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped) and peel a couple of the outer layers. Take the bit in the middle and whack it with something heavy to break it up a bit (and release that awesome lemony smell).

> TIP: It's important you chop, chop, chop the lemongrass to make sure it cooks perfectly.

Toss the @beef strips{240%g} in a #mixing bowl{} together with a sprinkle of @salt{}, a good pinch of @black pepper{} and the @cornflour{5%g}. Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on high heat. Once the oil is nice and hot, gently place the steak slices into the pan. Stir-fry for ~{2%minutes}. Remove the steak from the pan and keep to one side.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in the now empty #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the whites of the spring onion, chilli (add more or less to taste), garlic and lemongrass. Cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the green beans and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, ~{5%minutes}. Add the @soy sauce{50%ml}, @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp}, a pinch of @?sugar{} (if you have some) and a splash of @water{} together with the steak. Toss everything in the #pan{} for another ~{2%minutes}.

Drain the rice, then fluff it up with a #fork{} and spoon into #bowls{}. Serve the steak stir-fry on top of the rice with a sprinkling of the green parts of the spring onion. BOOM, you're done!